Your goroutines are now launching concurrently, but `main()` will likely exit before they finish!

Write a second loop in `main()` to receive the results from the channel. Since you started 5 goroutines, loop 5 times:

```go
for i := 0; i < len(urls); i++ {
    result := <-ch
    if result.Error != nil {
        fmt.Println("Error fetching", result.URL)
        continue
    }
    fmt.Printf("%s fetched in %v\n", result.URL, result.ElapsedTime)
}
```
